#!/usr/bin/env dothttp

# imported from descriptionobject.postman_collection.json

// The Directions API is a web service that uses an HTTP request to return JSON or XML-formatted directions between locations. You can receive directions for several modes of transportation, such as transit, driving, walking, or cycling.

@name("directions")
GET "https://maps.googleapis.com/maps/api/directions/json"
? "arrival_time"= "<number>"
? "departure_time"= "<number>"
? "alternatives"= "<boolean>"
? "avoid"= "<string>"
? "destination"= "<string>"
? "origin"= "<string>"
? "waypoints"= "<string>"
? "language"= "en"
? "mode"= "<string>"
? "region"= "en"
? "traffic_model"= "best_guess"
? "transit_mode"= "<string>"
? "transit_routing_preference"= "<string>"
? "units"= "<string>"
